s [[Administration (government)|administrated]] by a [[Sarpanch]] who is an [[elected representative]].\n\n== Transport ==\nKapurthala Rail Way Station, Rail Coach Fact Rail Way Station are the very nearby railway stations however, Jalandhar City Rail Way station is 23&nbsp;km away from the village. The village is 73&nbsp;km away from [[Sri Guru Ram Dass Jee International Airport]] in [[Amritsar]] and the another nearest airport is [[Sahnewal Airport]]  in [[Ludhiana]] which is located 77&nbsp;km away from the village.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n<!-- Please Note: Do not add any promotional\n information on this page. Any promotional/spam\n Links or any other information added will be\n removed immediately -->\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/Listofvillagesandtowns.aspx  Villages in Kapurthala]\n* [https://www.punjabdata.com/Villages/Villages-In-Kapurthala-Tehsil-In-Kapurthala-District.html Kapurthala Villages List]\n\n{{Kapurthala district |state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Kapurthala district]]\n\n\n{{PunjabIN-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "SDZeroBot", "label": "safe", "comment": "Stub sorting: replacing PunjabIN-geo-stub with Kapurthala-geo-stub", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saido_Bholana"}
{"title_page": "1931 Quebec general election", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=July 2009}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name      = 1931 Quebec general election\n| country            = Quebec\n| type               = parliamentary\n| ongoing            = no\n| party_colour       = no\n| party_name         = no\n| previous_election  = 1927 Quebec general election\n| previous_year      = 1927\n| previous_mps       = 17th Quebec Legislature\n| next_election      = 1935 Quebec general election\n| next_year          = 1935\n| next_mps           = 18th Quebec Legislature\n| seats_for_election = 90 seats in the [[18th Legislative Assembly of Quebec]] <br /> 46 seats were needed for a majority\n| election_date      = August 24, 1931\n\n| image1             = File:Louis-Alexandre Taschereau - 1930.png\n| image1_size        = 150x150px\n| colour1            = {{Canadian party colour|QC|Liberal|nohash}}\n| leader1            = [[Louis-Alexandre Taschereau]]\n| leader_since1      = 1920\n| party1             = {{Canadian party colour|QC|Liberal|name}}\n| leaders_seat1      = [[Montmorency (provincial electoral district)|Montmorency]]\n| last_election1     = 74 seats, 59.33%\n| seats1             = '''79'''\n| seat_change1       = {{increase}}5\n| popular_vote1      = \n| percentage1        = '''54.88%'''\n| swing1             = {{decrease}}4.45[[Percentage point|pp]]\n\n| image2             = Camillien Houde.jpg\n| image2_size        = 150x150px\n| colour2            = {{Canadian party colour|QC|Conservative (historical)|nohash}}\n| leader2            = [[Camillien Houde]]\n| leader_since2      = 1929\n| party2             = {{Canadian party colour|QC|Conservative (historical)|name}}\n| leaders_seat2      = ''Ran in [[Montr\u00e9al\u2013Saint-Jacques]] (defeated)''\n| last_election2     = 9 seats, 34.31%\n| seats2             = 11\n| seat_change2       = {{increase}}2\n| popular_vote2      = \n| percentage2        = 43.54%\n| swing2             = {{increase}}9.23[[Percentage point|pp]]\n\n| map_image          =\n| map_size           =\n| map_caption        =\n| title              = Premier\n| before_election    = [[Louis-Alexandre Taschereau]]\n| before_party       = {{Canadian party colour|QC|Liberal|name}}\n| after_election     = [[Louis-Alexandre Taschereau]]\n| posttitle          = Premier after election\n| after_party        = {{Canadian party colour|QC|Liberal|name}}\n}}\nThe '''1931 Quebec general election''' was held on August 24, 1931 to elect members of the [[National Assembly of Quebec|Legislative Assembly]] of the Province of [[Quebec]], Canada.  The incumbent [[Quebec Liberal Party]], led by [[Louis-Alexandre Taschereau]], was re-elected, defeating the [[Conservative Party of Quebec (historical)|Quebec Conservative Party]], led by [[Camillien Houde]].\n\nIt was the third general election victory in a row for Taschereau, who had held office since 1920.\n\n==Results==\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse border-color: #444444\"\n|- bgcolor=\"darkgray\"\n!rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"|Party\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Party leader\n!rowspan=\"2\"|# of<br />candidates\n!colspan=\"3\"|Seats\n!colspan=\"3\"|Popular Vote\n|- bgcolor=\"darkgray\"\n|align=\"center\"|[[1927 Quebec general election|1927]]\n|align=\"center\"|'''Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|% Change\n|align=\"center\"|#\n|align=\"center\"|%\n|align=\"center\"|% Change\n{{Canadian party colour|QC|Liberal|row-name}} \n| [[Louis-Alexandre Taschereau]] <!--leader-->\n|align=\"right\"|&nbsp;  <!--cand-->\n|align=\"right\"|74  <!--prev-->\n!align=\"right\"|79    <!--elected-->\n|align=\"right\"|+6.8%  <!--%ch.seats-->\n|align=\"right\"|&nbsp;   <!--vote-->\n|align=\"right\"| 54.88%   <!--%vote-->\n|align=\"right\"|-4.45%   <!--%ch.votes-->\n{{Canadian party colour|QC|Conservative (historical)|row-name}} \n|  [[Camillien Houde]]  <!--leader-->\n|align=\"right\"|&nbsp;   <!--cand-->\n|align=\"right\"| 9  <!--prev-->\n!align=\"right\"| 11 